    "valid": true,
    "description": "Old managed disks that are no longer linked to any virtual machine can still generate storage charges every month. This workflow runs across **all selected subscriptions and selected regions**, identifies such disks, validates that they are safe to remove, calculates potential cost savings, and adds them to **Opportunities**.\n\n## How It Works\n\n- Enumerate all managed disks in the **selected subscriptions and regions**.  \n- Filter for disks that have **no VM ID** (unattached).  \n- For each unattached disk:  \n  - Verify that **no snapshots or images** depend on it.  \n  - If all validation checks pass, calculate the potential savings.  \n  - Add the disk as a cost-saving opportunity.\n\n## Required Azure Permissions\n\n- `Microsoft.Compute/disks/read`  \n- `Microsoft.Compute/disks/delete`  \n- `Microsoft.Compute/snapshots/read`  \n- `Microsoft.Compute/images/read`  \n- `Microsoft.Resources/subscriptions/resourceGroups/read`"
  },
